00:19:44.301 --> 00:19:48.185
chest and then stood over the
body to make sure that she was

00:19:48.185 --> 00:19:50.818
dead before calling an
ambulance.

00:19:50.818 --> 00:19:55.566
Imagine the strength of the
cultural norms that allows a

00:19:55.566 --> 00:19:59.708
brother to kill a sister,
or a father to kill his

00:19:59.708 --> 00:20:00.828
daughter.
 

00:20:00.828 --> 00:20:03.545
In this last case,
this woman who the father

00:20:03.545 --> 00:20:06.598
killed her,
the family was not poor and was

00:20:06.598 --> 00:20:09.403
not Muslim,
even though it's in Jordan but

00:20:09.403 --> 00:20:12.118
they were middle class and Roman
Catholic.

00:20:12.118 --> 00:20:16.413
So that means--almost nobody in
these cultures escapes the

00:20:16.413 --> 00:20:20.632
cultural norms even though
Catholics in Jordan are a very

00:20:20.632 --> 00:20:24.548
small minority as is the middle
class in Jordan.

00:20:24.548 --> 00:20:29.848
They obey the same rules of the
culture as everyone else.

00:20:29.848 --> 00:20:33.615
The author of that book claims
that this happens to thousands

00:20:33.615 --> 00:20:37.317
of women, that there's thousands
of women dying in honor--so

00:20:37.317 --> 00:20:38.950
called honor killings.
 

00:20:38.950 --> 00:20:40.830
Now, of course,
it's not restricted to the

00:20:40.830 --> 00:20:43.500
Middle East,
you will read a little bit

00:20:43.500 --> 00:20:47.614
later a reading for India where
