because we do have a lot more
births than deaths,

00:32:03.422 --> 00:32:05.890
and I showed you that data
before.

00:32:05.890 --> 00:32:09.803
Malnutrition is the leading
cause of death in children in

00:32:09.803 --> 00:32:15.193
developing countries,
and the numbers you read are

00:32:15.193 --> 00:32:20.397
all over the place,
and one number that I pulled

00:32:20.397 --> 00:32:25.667
out is 13 million child deaths a
year and I've seen lower than

00:32:25.667 --> 00:32:26.358
that.
 

00:32:26.358 --> 00:32:29.990
The World Bank in the--it's
millennium goals,

00:32:29.990 --> 00:32:32.146
you know the big millennium
goal thing what the whole world

00:32:32.146 --> 00:32:34.856
is supposed to go to,
says again, that half the

00:32:34.856 --> 00:32:39.220
deaths of children under five
are due to malnutrition and--

00:32:39.220 --> 00:32:41.298
there's altogether,
for all reasons,

00:32:41.298 --> 00:32:45.590
there's 13 million child deaths
a year and you get numbers from

00:32:45.590 --> 00:32:49.327
different studies saying
anywhere between a third and a

00:32:49.327 --> 00:32:52.720
half of these deaths are due to
malnutrition.

00:32:52.720 --> 00:32:54.130
What does malnutrition look
like?

00:32:54.130 --> 00:33:00.983
You may have seen--this is
kwashiorkor, how many of you

00:33:00.983 --> 00:33:03.650
have heard of that?
 

00:33:03.650 --> 00:33:04.660
It's a very prevalent kind of
thing.

00:33:04.660 --> 00:33:05.808
Do I have a slide?
 

00:33:05.808 --> 00:33:10.105
You go to a village in poor
places and you see these

00:33:10.105 --> 00:33:11.788
distended bellies?
 

00:33:11.788 --> 00:33:15.554
This is everywhere and actually
we don't even--in --there's a

00:33:15.554 --> 00:33:19.006
tremendously prevalent thing,
we don't actually know the

00:33:19.006 --> 00:33:20.009
cause of it.
 

00:33:20.009 --> 00:33:24.117
The old story was that it's a
protein deficiency disease and

00:33:24.117 --> 00:33:27.808
protein makes albumin and
albumin holds water into the

00:33:27.808 --> 00:33:31.736
blood and the tissues,
and when you can't hold water,

00:33:31.736 --> 00:33:35.420
it sort of floods into your
tissues and spreads out,

00:33:35.420 --> 00:33:39.170
but now there's a lot of other
theories and we just don't know

00:33:39.170 --> 00:33:42.058
really what's the basic cause of
kwashiorkor.

00:33:42.058 --> 00:33:43.484
It is malnutrition.
 

00:33:43.484 --> 00:33:47.688
That's--there's no question
about it, but exactly what in

00:33:47.688 --> 00:33:50.990
the diet is missing is not
totally clear.

00:33:50.990 --> 00:33:55.046
Here's another kind of shocking
thing, now I'm going to give you

00:33:55.046 --> 00:33:58.651
some shocking pictures and
tearjerkers but it's important

00:33:58.651 --> 00:33:59.359
to see.
 

00:33:59.359 --> 00:34:01.519
This you've seen.
 

00:34:01.519 --> 00:34:05.075
This is an American missionary
or aid worker,

00:34:05.075 --> 00:34:09.762
I don't know which and that's
her baby and that's this baby

00:34:09.762 --> 00:34:13.480
and they're both six months old
in Africa.

00:34:13.480 --> 00:34:17.960
Another thing that happens is
that population--

00:34:17.960 --> 00:34:21.503
when population grows the
people who are strongest take

00:34:21.503 --> 00:34:25.639
the best land and they push out
people that are less strong,

00:34:25.639 --> 00:34:28.320
or have less population or are
less violent or whatever reason,

00:34:28.320 --> 00:34:31.342
or less technologically
advanced, they push them into

00:34:31.342 --> 00:34:33.030
marginal land like deserts.
 

00:34:33.030 --> 00:34:37.503
This is the site in Mali of
what used to be one of the

00:34:37.503 --> 00:34:42.231
largest lakes in Africa and then
it goes through periodic

00:34:42.231 --> 00:34:45.820
climatic things;
it dries out every so often.

00:34:45.820 --> 00:34:48.623
In some sense,
people should not be living

00:34:48.623 --> 00:34:51.360
there because you know it's
going to--

00:34:51.360 --> 00:34:53.030
it goes every so often through
droughts,

00:34:53.030 --> 00:34:56.230
but they have no choice because
stronger people's in the past

00:34:56.230 --> 00:34:59.110
have pushed them into these
desert kind of regions,

00:34:59.110 --> 00:35:01.710
one of the results of
population explosion.

00:35:01.710 --> 00:35:04.340
I've told you,
in Europe, where the extra

00:35:04.340 --> 00:35:08.550
farmers had to go up hillsides
and into less profitable land,

00:35:08.550 --> 00:35:14.001
so there they are in this very
arid region and in normal years

00:35:14.001 --> 00:35:17.784
they can survive,
but then comes a drought and

00:35:17.784 --> 00:35:20.920
this kind of thing happens and
the result,

00:35:20.920 --> 00:35:24.490
of course--this is a boy who is
I think nine years old or

00:35:24.490 --> 00:35:29.306
something,
he's 13 pounds and almost

00:35:29.306 --> 00:35:34.889
impossible to keep that boy
alive.

00:35:34.889 --> 00:35:38.369
Here's one of the really
saddening pictures that--

00:35:38.369 --> 00:35:43.150
in the political discourse
about population,

00:35:43.150 --> 00:35:45.715
and fertility,
and family planning in America

00:35:45.715 --> 00:35:49.927
there's a lot about motherhood,
how wonderful motherhood is --

00:35:49.927 --> 00:35:53.469
everything but you have to see--
well I didn't show that.

00:35:53.469 --> 00:35:57.871
I've got--I put in the wrong
picture which is maybe good for

00:35:57.871 --> 00:35:58.320
you.
 

00:35:58.320 --> 00:36:00.409
Now you've seen a lot of these
pictures.

00:36:00.409 --> 00:36:03.032
The organizations,
they want you to give money

00:36:03.032 --> 00:36:06.590
show a lot of them and one of
the discussion items about these

00:36:06.590 --> 00:36:09.971
kind of pictures is that they
make people in poor countries

00:36:09.971 --> 00:36:12.768
seem sort of helpless and that's
not true.

00:36:12.768 --> 00:36:16.253
The amount of stuff that people
in these countries are doing to

00:36:16.253 --> 00:36:18.389
try to help themselves is
enormous,

00:36:18.389 --> 00:36:20.139
they can be very strong and
very smart people,

00:36:20.139 --> 00:36:27.539
but their resources are very
limited what they work with.

00:36:27.539 --> 00:36:34.121
The bottom line of this little
bit is that given the number of

00:36:34.121 --> 00:36:40.813
deaths that we understand to be
from malnutrition and given the

00:36:40.813 --> 00:36:47.286
number of population increase,
if the solution is to be solved

00:36:47.286 --> 00:36:49.530
by famine,
if the balancing of births and

00:36:49.530 --> 00:36:51.250
deaths is going to be a famine
situation,

00:36:51.250 --> 00:36:55.340
the starvation rate must
increase by a factor of eight,

00:36:55.340 --> 00:36:57.960
plus or minus.
 

00:36:57.960 --> 00:37:01.913
The next thing is disease;
disease is the second of our

00:37:01.913 --> 00:37:03.710
triplet of horrible solutions.
 

00:37:03.710 --> 00:37:07.005
In 2008 it killed about three
million people,

00:37:07.005 --> 00:37:10.826
up from two million,
and this is clearly--apparently

00:37:10.826 --> 00:37:11.800
the peak.
 

00:37:11.800 --> 00:37:15.668
Everyone apparently--Because of
the retrovirals and various

00:37:15.668 --> 00:37:19.469
other public health measures,
the number is supposed to go

00:37:19.469 --> 00:37:20.070
down.
 

00:37:20.070 --> 00:37:22.460
The numbers are already
changing.

00:37:22.460 --> 00:37:26.623
At the end of 2007,
the UN got a whole bunch of

00:37:26.623 --> 00:37:31.510
better data from certain
countries and they had to--

00:37:31.510 --> 00:37:36.331
they lowered the number of
people they thought to be

00:37:36.331 --> 00:37:40.679
infected with the AIDS virus by
6.3 million.

00:37:40.679 --> 00:37:44.860
So something like 33 million
people infected with AIDS,

00:37:44.860 --> 00:37:47.829
and presumably they will all
die at some point,

00:37:47.829 --> 00:37:51.349
although the retrovirals can
keep them alive a long time.

00:37:51.349 --> 00:37:56.150
Notice that 33 million is less
than half of one year's

00:37:56.150 --> 00:37:58.869
population growth from AIDS.
 

00:37:58.869 --> 00:38:04.190
It's--the way it works out
demographically is here is

00:38:04.190 --> 00:38:10.175
somewhat older data at the--
from the peak of the AIDS

00:38:10.175 --> 00:38:12.992
epidemic,
this is the impact in

00:38:12.992 --> 00:38:16.130
Sub-Saharan Africa with and
without AIDS,

00:38:16.130 --> 00:38:23.306
so the gray--the purple is the
way the population -was modeled

00:38:23.306 --> 00:38:27.965
to increase without AIDS,
as if there was no AIDS,

00:38:27.965 --> 00:38:30.554
and then with AIDS,
AIDS kills these people

00:38:30.554 --> 00:38:32.679
basically, prevents these
births,

00:38:32.679 --> 00:38:36.240
you still have an enormous
population increase for

00:38:36.240 --> 00:38:40.239
Sub-Saharan Africa which is the
worst affected place.

00:38:40.239 --> 00:38:43.670
This is one of the worst
scenarios --they did a worst

00:38:43.670 --> 00:38:47.429
case scenario run which they
sort of imagined things to be

00:38:47.429 --> 00:38:49.739
about as bad as they could get.
 

00:38:49.739 --> 00:38:53.340
This thing, when you do it for
a whole--most of a continent

00:38:53.340 --> 00:38:56.594
hides a lot of difference;
this is Uganda,

00:38:56.594 --> 00:39:02.349
which had a very intelligent
response to AIDS and here,

00:39:02.349 --> 00:39:05.043
with AIDS there will be this
much, and without AIDS there

00:39:05.043 --> 00:39:08.199
would have been this much,
but population keeps growing.

00:39:08.199 --> 00:39:10.007
In any case,
in South Africa,

00:39:10.007 --> 00:39:14.010
which is about the worst really
badly hit place you do see that

00:39:14.010 --> 00:39:17.561
population growth without AIDS
would be this and they're

00:39:17.561 --> 00:39:21.436
actually expecting population
growth to come down as a result

00:39:21.436 --> 00:39:22.469
of AIDS.
 

00:39:22.469 --> 00:39:25.746
In some countries,
it has an important demographic

00:39:25.746 --> 00:39:28.824
effect, but for Sub-Saharan
Africa, as a whole,

00:39:28.824 --> 00:39:30.630
not an enormous effect.
 

00:39:30.630 --> 00:39:33.114
In the rest of world,
where, at least so far,

00:39:33.114 --> 00:39:35.768
the numbers are much smaller,
a minor effect.

00:39:35.768 --> 00:39:38.516
It can easily get lost in the
statistical noise that we don't

00:39:38.516 --> 00:39:40.210
know how many people are on
earth,

00:39:40.210 --> 00:39:45.456
we don't know exactly how fast
the population is growing and

00:39:45.456 --> 00:39:49.369
AIDS can be within that
statistical noise.

00:39:49.369 --> 00:39:55.369
From a demographic point of
view, AIDS as a killer,

00:39:55.369 --> 00:39:57.409
is significant.
 

00:39:57.409 --> 00:40:01.695
Let me show you there's another
thing that kills 1.6 million

00:40:01.695 --> 00:40:04.820
people more than half of the
AIDS number.

00:40:04.820 --> 00:40:08.730
You'll never guess what that is?
 

00:40:08.730 --> 00:40:12.780
It's this, it's smoke from
cooking fires,

00:40:12.780 --> 00:40:15.103
that in the developing
countries, in the poor

00:40:15.103 --> 00:40:17.702
countries,
this is the way people cook and

00:40:17.702 --> 00:40:20.731
the smoke fills the room,
gets into their lungs,

00:40:20.731 --> 00:40:24.257
and they get all kinds of
diseases extra and the estimates

00:40:24.257 --> 00:40:28.918
of that is 1.6 million deaths;
comparable to tuberculosis and

00:40:28.918 --> 00:40:32.150
malaria and somewhat less than
AIDS.

00:40:32.150 --> 00:40:36.443
They have a solution to this
and it's a stove that

00:40:36.443 --> 00:40:41.090
keeps--that you don't get these
kind of smoke with.

00:40:41.090 --> 00:40:46.340
And those cost $10 each and
they'll cut out a number of

00:40:46.340 --> 00:40:50.909
deaths equivalent to half of the
AIDS deaths.

00:40:50.909 --> 00:40:54.286
One of the things--if you're
interested in understanding the

00:40:54.286 --> 00:40:56.690
magnitude of the problems of the
world,

00:40:56.690 --> 00:40:59.742
one of the things you just have
to pay attention is the

00:40:59.742 --> 00:41:03.190
magnitude of the problem and the
magnitude of any solution.

00:41:03.190 --> 00:41:08.056
When there's an almost sure
thing of $10 available and

00:41:08.056 --> 00:41:13.476
retrovirals cost an awful lot
more, which kind of person are

00:41:13.476 --> 00:41:16.139
you going to try to save?
 

00:41:16.139 --> 00:41:19.920
The person that can be saved by
$10 or the person that needs

00:41:19.920 --> 00:41:23.510
$1,000 to be saved if you have
limited kinds of money.

00:41:23.510 --> 00:41:28.400
From a demographic point of
view the problem with--

00:41:28.400 --> 00:41:31.632
almost worse than the total
number of deaths because

00:41:31.632 --> 00:41:34.739
malaria's been killing people
for a long time,

00:41:34.739 --> 00:41:36.800
and TB and these are all
horrible situations,

00:41:36.800 --> 00:41:39.860
of course every death is a
horrible sort of thing,

00:41:39.860 --> 00:41:44.989
but AIDS kills people in the
prime of their life and that's--

00:41:44.989 --> 00:41:47.731
this is what we call hollowing
out of the Age structure so

00:41:47.731 --> 00:41:49.559
there's children who are
dependent,

00:41:49.559 --> 00:41:52.045
there's adults who work and
there's old people who are

00:41:52.045 --> 00:41:52.610
dependent.
 

00:41:52.610 --> 00:41:56.650
If you kill off your working
people that leaves the kids with

00:41:56.650 --> 00:42:00.393
no one to take care of them,
no one to provide economically

00:42:00.393 --> 00:42:03.411
for them,
that leaves the old people with

00:42:03.411 --> 00:42:05.670
no one to take care of them.
 

00:42:05.670 --> 00:42:12.929
The direct deaths from AIDS
itself is one horrible thing,

00:42:12.929 --> 00:42:17.637
but what they do to taking care
of everybody else in the

00:42:17.637 --> 00:42:21.489
population multiples that effect
by a lot,

00:42:21.489 --> 00:42:24.860
and as of 2001 the last
statistics that I could find,

00:42:24.860 --> 00:42:29.822
there's about 12 million
children that have been orphaned

00:42:29.822 --> 00:42:31.949
in Africa due to AIDS.
 

00:42:31.949 --> 00:42:36.130
That is--we do a lot of work in
the political refugees,

00:42:36.130 --> 00:42:40.465
that's triple the number of
political refugees that there

00:42:40.465 --> 00:42:41.860
are in Africa.
 

00:42:41.860 --> 00:42:45.659
We've done famine,
disease, and wars is the last

00:42:45.659 --> 00:42:50.431
set of numbers and you hear it
at cocktail parties that some

00:42:50.431 --> 00:42:52.918
war,
whatever the current war is,

00:42:52.918 --> 00:42:54.929
will balance births and deaths.
 

00:42:54.929 --> 00:42:58.250
The worst we've had is the atom
bombs,

00:42:58.250 --> 00:43:01.163
and I don't know if you know
what the numbers on the atom

00:43:01.163 --> 00:43:03.972
bombs are,
but the Hiroshima bomb killed

00:43:03.972 --> 00:43:07.668
75,000 people,
the Nagasaki bomb killed 25,000

00:43:07.668 --> 00:43:08.320
people.
 

00:43:08.320 --> 00:43:14.780
That's 100,000 people dead in
two quick flashes.

00:43:14.780 --> 00:43:20.989
The population on earth grows
by approximately 200,000 a day.

00:43:20.989 --> 00:43:22.949
What that means is that,
if we can imagine,

00:43:22.949 --> 00:43:27.032
and all these are imaginary,
if we imagine that some wars

00:43:27.032 --> 00:43:31.552
are going to balance births and
deaths on earth that means that

00:43:31.552 --> 00:43:35.563
every day you have to blow up
two Nagasaki bombs and two

00:43:35.563 --> 00:43:38.672
Hiroshima bombs,
killing that equivalent number

00:43:38.672 --> 00:43:40.059
of people just to keep even.
 

00:43:40.059 --> 00:43:44.949
That doesn't reduce population,
that just keeps population

00:43:44.949 --> 00:43:45.550
flat.
 

00:43:45.550 --> 00:43:50.023
The idea of giving you all
these horrible numbers is just

00:43:50.023 --> 00:43:54.657
to give you an idea of the
magnitude of this issue and that

00:43:54.657 --> 00:43:58.891
it's of course absolutely
unthinkable that one sort of

00:43:58.891 --> 00:44:03.525
continues to just let this
situation go rampantly until one

00:44:03.525 --> 00:44:07.679
of these negative kind of
disasters happens.

00:44:07.679 --> 00:44:11.179
There's got to be a solution.
 

00:44:11.179 --> 00:44:16.139
We have to figure it out in
some way.

00:44:16.139 --> 00:44:19.572
So far in the last lecture or
so, I've obviously been what we

00:44:19.572 --> 00:44:20.659
call apocalyptic.
 

00:44:20.659 --> 00:44:26.809
The world is coming to an end
due to population explosion,

00:44:26.809 --> 00:44:30.159
but there's a famous saying to
the opposite,

00:44:30.159 --> 00:44:32.949
which is that if something
can't go on forever,

00:44:32.949 --> 00:44:34.989
it won't.
 

00:44:34.989 --> 00:44:40.702
I think that has a large chance
of happening and I've described

00:44:40.702 --> 00:44:46.231
some of this already to you in
our last lecture and I'm going

00:44:46.231 --> 00:44:49.550
to talk more about it right now.
 

00:44:49.550 --> 00:44:54.432
Consider these two interviews,
one is an interview very much

00:44:54.432 --> 00:44:58.985
like one of the ones in your
readings, it's from Mali in

00:44:58.985 --> 00:45:00.309
1983, Sitan.
 

00:45:00.309 --> 00:45:04.400
This is a woman who's heard
about the contraceptive pill but

00:45:04.400 --> 00:45:05.650
has not used it.
 

00:45:05.650 --> 00:45:07.170
Interviewer:
"Sitan,

00:45:07.170 --> 00:45:10.590
how many children more would
you like to have?"

00:45:10.590 --> 00:45:13.570
"That is for God to
decide."

00:45:13.570 --> 00:45:14.980
Interviewer:
"You yourself,

00:45:14.980 --> 00:45:17.150
how many more children would
you like--

00:45:17.150 --> 00:45:20.240
how many children would you
like to have in your whole

00:45:20.240 --> 00:45:21.000
life?"
 

00:45:21.000 --> 00:45:22.179
"I don't know the number.
 

00:45:22.179 --> 00:45:26.059
It's when God stops my
births."

00:45:26.059 --> 00:45:27.474
Interviewer:
"How many boys and how

00:45:27.474 --> 00:45:29.000
many girls would you like to
have?"

00:45:29.000 --> 00:45:30.340
"It's God that gives me
children.

00:45:30.340 --> 00:45:34.001
Since it is God that gives or
not, you cannot make a choice

00:45:34.001 --> 00:45:35.768
about your children."
 

00:45:35.768 --> 00:45:37.280
You've read some of these,
this is a different country,

00:45:37.280 --> 00:45:40.929
a different time,
but this is a not uncommon sort

00:45:40.929 --> 00:45:44.913
of attitude where people,
women especially,

00:45:44.913 --> 00:45:50.798
just can't--it's not within
their calculus of conscious

00:45:50.798 --> 00:45:51.889
choice.
 

00:45:51.889 --> 00:45:54.927
Now in Bangladesh,
which is again,

00:45:54.927 --> 00:45:59.809
both of these countries are
Muslim, Bangladesh is more

00:45:59.809 --> 00:46:02.480
conservative religiously.
 

00:46:02.480 --> 00:46:07.449
The poverty getting better now,
but it was about the same,

00:46:07.449 --> 00:46:11.231
so there's the socioeconomic
indicators for the two countries

00:46:11.231 --> 00:46:14.112
are about the same,
but the government in

00:46:14.112 --> 00:46:17.739
Bangladesh was very different
and the government,

00:46:17.739 --> 00:46:21.407
from very early on,
decided that they would make

00:46:21.407 --> 00:46:26.168
family planning available in the
country and the international

00:46:26.168 --> 00:46:29.289
groups then came on board and
said,

00:46:29.289 --> 00:46:33.400
okay, we will help you.
 

00:46:33.400 --> 00:46:37.746
This is now another interview
with an 18 year old girl named

00:46:37.746 --> 00:46:41.650
Shamiran and she is just
learning that there is such a

00:46:41.650 --> 00:46:43.639
thing as birth control.
 

00:46:43.639 --> 00:46:47.010
The reason she knows about it
is that,

00:46:47.010 --> 00:46:49.943
and you'll read about--you're
going to read about the family

00:46:49.943 --> 00:46:52.429
planning program and the results
in Bangladesh,

00:46:52.429 --> 00:46:55.440
is that as I said Bangladesh is
a very conservative Muslim

00:46:55.440 --> 00:46:55.969
country.
 

00:46:55.969 --> 00:46:59.469
So, women generally are not
allowed out of the house to get

00:46:59.469 --> 00:47:01.340
medical service for instance.
 

00:47:01.340 --> 00:47:03.773
Just to go out and talk to
women's meetings where these

00:47:03.773 --> 00:47:04.809
things get discussed.
 

00:47:04.809 --> 00:47:06.369
No. They can't do that.
 

00:47:06.369 --> 00:47:10.030
The family planning program in
Bangladesh,

00:47:10.030 --> 00:47:11.929
the government program and the
private program,

00:47:11.929 --> 00:47:15.739
hired high class women from
that community,

00:47:15.739 --> 00:47:19.898
who themselves were using
family planning and thought it

00:47:19.898 --> 00:47:24.056
was good and sent them into the
houses of poor women who

00:47:24.056 --> 00:47:25.719
couldn't come out.
 

00:47:25.719 --> 00:47:28.309
This is kind of like if
Muhammad--the mountain won't

00:47:28.309 --> 00:47:30.340
come to Muhammad,
Muhammad will go to the

00:47:30.340 --> 00:47:31.000
mountain.
 

00:47:31.000 --> 00:47:33.639
The people in the village all
know about this woman who,

00:47:33.639 --> 00:47:36.949
Mukti Ma, that was her name,
and she's considered a health

00:47:36.949 --> 00:47:39.329
worker and she actually gave her
aunt,

00:47:39.329 --> 00:47:42.860
her aunt was an acceptor and
Mukti Ma was giving--

00:47:42.860 --> 00:47:46.961
came by regularly to give her
aunt pills and the girls knew

00:47:46.961 --> 00:47:47.739
about it.
 

00:47:47.739 --> 00:47:50.873
But they didn't really
understand it and so they went

00:47:50.873 --> 00:47:53.384
and asked the aunt,
the girl Shamiran,

00:47:53.384 --> 00:47:57.199
and the aunt refused to tell
her anything because again the

00:47:57.199 --> 00:48:00.239
social conservatism,
that these matters will be

00:48:00.239 --> 00:48:03.722
explained to her only when she
is married and she's not to know

00:48:03.722 --> 00:48:05.239
anything about this now.
 

00:48:05.239 --> 00:48:06.469
What did the kid do?
 

00:48:06.469 --> 00:48:08.762
Like every kid everywhere else
in the world she goes to school

00:48:08.762 --> 00:48:12.197
and talks with her friends,
and they all pick little bits

00:48:12.197 --> 00:48:17.054
of information or misinformation
and pull it together from the

00:48:17.054 --> 00:48:18.250
other girls.
 

00:48:18.250 --> 00:48:21.273
Some of them apparently knew of
Mukti Ma, some of them didn't

00:48:21.273 --> 00:48:22.130
know about her.
 

00:48:22.130 --> 00:48:23.510
I'm sorry I said everyone in
the village knows,

00:48:23.510 --> 00:48:27.291
apparently they didn't,
but since this girl's aunt was

00:48:27.291 --> 00:48:30.789
getting pills from Mukti Ma she
knew about it,

00:48:30.789 --> 00:48:33.530
but every one of her
schoolmates was interested.

00:48:33.530 --> 00:48:36.289
One girl said,
"I would like to work as

00:48:36.289 --> 00:48:38.280
she does,"
she Mukti Ma.

00:48:38.280 --> 00:48:40.952
"Look at her,
she wears her sari so nicely

00:48:40.952 --> 00:48:43.159
and goes to different
neighborhoods.

00:48:43.159 --> 00:48:46.280
My sister told me she earns a
good amount of money."

00:48:46.280 --> 00:48:48.755
Others said,
"but my father and

00:48:48.755 --> 00:48:52.079
grandmother says she's not a
good lady."

00:48:52.079 --> 00:48:54.947
Shamiran said,
"Grandmothers and fathers

00:48:54.947 --> 00:48:58.393
are always behind the times,
they do not want to let girls

00:48:58.393 --> 00:49:00.987
go to school,
I don't want to consider their

00:49:00.987 --> 00:49:03.487
opinions,
I like Mukti Ma's work and I

00:49:03.487 --> 00:49:06.150
will have pills to control
births."

00:49:06.150 --> 00:49:08.782
Some girls said,
"Yes, I think we should

00:49:08.782 --> 00:49:12.313
have this medicine so we will
not have so many problems with

00:49:12.313 --> 00:49:13.570
so many children.
 

00:49:13.570 --> 00:49:17.050
With few children,
we'll be able to keep our saris

00:49:17.050 --> 00:49:20.742
clean and nice,"
Then everybody laughed together

00:49:20.742 --> 00:49:23.940
and that apparently ended that
interview.

00:49:23.940 --> 00:49:28.987
This is an older generation
versus a younger generation and

00:49:28.987 --> 00:49:32.119
there's an interest of the
girls,

00:49:32.119 --> 00:49:34.572
as they self perceive it,
and the interest of the older

00:49:34.572 --> 00:49:37.320
generation,
as they are trying to impose it

00:49:37.320 --> 00:49:39.159
on the younger generation.
 

00:49:39.159 --> 00:49:42.010
It's a very clear kind of a
conflict situation.

00:49:42.010 --> 00:49:44.456
The girls see having many
children as just causing a lot

00:49:44.456 --> 00:49:47.172
of problems and what the girls
are interested in is not having

00:49:47.172 --> 00:49:49.545
a lot of children as--
which was terribly important to

00:49:49.545 --> 00:49:50.980
their--
certainly their grandparents

00:49:50.980 --> 00:49:52.099
and probably their parents.
 

00:49:52.099 --> 00:49:55.329
They want to have nice clean
saris and look nice.

00:49:55.329 --> 00:49:59.371
They want to be able to earn
money and go around to different

00:49:59.371 --> 00:50:00.449
neighborhoods.
 

00:50:00.449 --> 00:50:04.485
The older generation is trying
to keep them out of school,

00:50:04.485 --> 00:50:08.876
keep this information away from
them, and keep them in the mold

00:50:08.876 --> 00:50:09.940
previously.
 

00:50:09.940 --> 00:50:14.601
The girls in that society are
pretty much powerless because

00:50:14.601 --> 00:50:18.219
even though the age at marriage
has risen,

00:50:18.219 --> 00:50:21.467
Shamiran's already 18,
which traditionally is terribly

00:50:21.467 --> 00:50:23.489
old for a girl to be unmarried.
 

00:50:23.489 --> 00:50:26.369
She'll eventually get married,
moved in with her husband,

00:50:26.369 --> 00:50:29.802
and the husband will also be a
teenager probably and will have

00:50:29.802 --> 00:50:33.652
not much say --
the husband's mother will be

00:50:33.652 --> 00:50:38.168
the arbiter of medical things,
reproductive things,

00:50:38.168 --> 00:50:41.614
so that both the son and the
daughter-in-law will be under

00:50:41.614 --> 00:50:45.059
the control primarily of the
mother-in-law and so it's the

00:50:45.059 --> 00:50:47.599
mother-in-law's opinions that
count,

00:50:47.599 --> 00:50:51.199
the mother-in-law's attitude
toward reproduction that counts.

00:50:51.199 --> 00:50:53.266
Very often we,
in the west,

00:50:53.266 --> 00:50:56.012
say that--
the problem is all with men,

00:50:56.012 --> 00:50:59.985
the macho men force women into
having children and some of that

00:50:59.985 --> 00:51:03.893
is certainly true and sometimes
in Latin America a fair amount

00:51:03.893 --> 00:51:07.742
of that can be true,
but in Asia it's very often the

00:51:07.742 --> 00:51:08.800
mother-in-law.
 

00:51:08.800 --> 00:51:10.230
Wherever you see that the young
girl--

00:51:10.230 --> 00:51:12.880
they get married young,
the husband and wife are both

00:51:12.880 --> 00:51:15.596
young,
they move into the husband's

00:51:15.596 --> 00:51:18.820
house which is the grandparents
house,

00:51:18.820 --> 00:51:21.740
then the boy will be under
control of his mother and the

00:51:21.740 --> 00:51:24.768
new wife will be perhaps almost
a slave to that mother.

00:51:24.768 --> 00:51:27.699
You have many,
many instances where both the

00:51:27.699 --> 00:51:31.721
boy--the husband and the young
girl wife do not want to have

00:51:31.721 --> 00:51:34.719
children but they don't have any
choice.

00:51:34.719 --> 00:51:41.876
In matters of reproduction it's
mother-in-laws who are the

00:51:41.876 --> 00:51:49.659
dominant transmitters of culture
in the thing--in the world.

00:51:49.659 --> 00:51:53.393
I showed you in the data at the
beginning of last lecture that

00:51:53.393 --> 00:51:56.387
the Shamirans of the earth,
who are not so enamored of

00:51:56.387 --> 00:51:58.902
having a lot of children,
have taken over from the

00:51:58.902 --> 00:52:02.335
Sitan's of the earth,
who will have as many as

00:52:02.335 --> 00:52:04.420
they're going to have.
 

00:52:04.420 --> 00:52:08.541
The data was very strong that
women in the developing

00:52:08.541 --> 00:52:13.217
countries don't want all the
children that they're currently

00:52:13.217 --> 00:52:14.090
having.
 

00:52:14.090 --> 00:52:18.409
You've seen new data and you've
seen old data from that.

00:52:18.409 --> 00:52:20.010
I showed you Bolivia new data
you could--

00:52:20.010 --> 00:52:23.264
I can--you can come up to my
office and see the Demographic

00:52:23.264 --> 00:52:26.800
&amp; Health Surveys and pick a
country and it's pretty much all

00:52:26.800 --> 00:52:27.530
the same.
 

00:52:27.530 --> 00:52:30.503
With the exceptions of
Sub-Saharan Africa is somewhat

00:52:30.503 --> 00:52:33.018
exception and some of the Arab
countries,

00:52:33.018 --> 00:52:36.132
not the Muslim countries,
many Muslim countries have

00:52:36.132 --> 00:52:39.670
really reduced their fertility
but Arab countries are going

00:52:39.670 --> 00:52:41.929
through a non-standard
situation.

00:52:41.929 --> 00:52:47.016
This information has
been--we've had this since about

00:52:47.016 --> 00:52:48.190
the 1960s.
 

00:52:48.190 --> 00:52:51.996
We've had it for about a half a
century, knowledge that women in

00:52:51.996 --> 00:52:55.320
the developing world don't
really want the children that

00:52:55.320 --> 00:52:56.469
they're having.
 

00:52:56.469 --> 00:53:00.963
In the 1960s they started with
a survey called KAP,

00:53:00.963 --> 00:53:03.840
knowledge, attitude,
practice.

00:53:03.840 --> 00:53:06.869
Knowledge: did you know about
contraception?

00:53:06.869 --> 00:53:10.119
Attitude: do you want it,
what do you think about it?

00:53:10.119 --> 00:53:12.929
Practice: are you actually
using it?

00:53:12.929 --> 00:53:18.027
Then from 1972 to 1982 there
were surveys called The World

00:53:18.027 --> 00:53:23.036
Fertility Survey which were
improved from the KAP surveys

00:53:23.036 --> 00:53:28.940
and they reached 62 countries
with 350,000 women interviewed,

00:53:28.940 --> 00:53:32.726
and then from 1985 they've been
coming along with these

00:53:32.726 --> 00:53:35.250
Demographic &amp;
Health Surveys,

00:53:35.250 --> 00:53:37.969
which are more or less
standardized across the world,

00:53:37.969 --> 00:53:42.590
and from which the data I gave
you came.

00:53:42.590 --> 00:53:48.043
If you listen to the verbal
report of these women,

00:53:48.043 --> 00:53:52.719
they say they don't want these
children.

00:53:52.719 --> 00:53:55.777
The question--you have to
always question--scientists

00:53:55.777 --> 00:53:58.483
always question everything,
okay they say that,

00:53:58.483 --> 00:53:59.601
but how much oomph!
 

00:53:59.601 --> 00:54:00.659
is behind it?
 

00:54:00.659 --> 00:54:02.760
It could be an interviewer
comes in,

00:54:02.760 --> 00:54:05.612
obviously a very modern person,
you know that modern people

00:54:05.612 --> 00:54:08.710
sort of think that the modern
way is to have fewer children,

00:54:08.710 --> 00:54:12.123
so you may very well answer
them in that way so you can

00:54:12.123 --> 00:54:14.210
never be sure of these surveys.
 

00:54:14.210 --> 00:54:18.429
You always have to look at what
are people actually doing and

00:54:18.429 --> 00:54:22.860
there are various ways that you
can find out if this a real--

00:54:22.860 --> 00:54:27.590
a desire backed by behavior.
 

00:54:27.590 --> 00:54:31.922
One of the things is well how
permanent--of those women that

00:54:31.922 --> 00:54:35.007
choose some sort of family
planning method,

00:54:35.007 --> 00:54:36.769
how permanent is it?
 

00:54:36.769 --> 00:54:38.039
How good is it?
 

00:54:38.039 --> 00:54:43.012
It turns out that basically
everywhere in the world

00:54:43.012 --> 00:54:48.880
sterilization is the dominant
choice for family planning.

00:54:48.880 --> 00:54:52.472
In Brazil, for instance,
by the late 1980s and their

00:54:52.472 --> 00:54:55.079
fertility has come down from
then,

00:54:55.079 --> 00:55:00.431
40% of married women using
contraception in fact chose to

00:55:00.431 --> 00:55:04.539
be sterilized over all the other
methods.

00:55:04.539 --> 00:55:08.293
Now you might think that this
was the poorest women who chose

00:55:08.293 --> 00:55:10.860
this, that they were kind of
desperate.

00:55:10.860 --> 00:55:13.320
Maybe they were influenced by
family planning workers to just

00:55:13.320 --> 00:55:16.474
get it over with,
and I've heard polemical

00:55:16.474 --> 00:55:20.853
arguments saying that,
Oh, these sterilization things

00:55:20.853 --> 00:55:24.938
are because that was what was
pushed upon them by some family

00:55:24.938 --> 00:55:26.369
planning program'.
 

00:55:26.369 --> 00:55:30.481
In fact, statistics are very
clear that the higher the income

00:55:30.481 --> 00:55:33.907
level of the woman,
the greater likelihood that she

00:55:33.907 --> 00:55:36.099
was to choose sterilization.
 

00:55:36.099 --> 00:55:40.625
One of these--have any of you
seen this film about testing the

00:55:40.625 --> 00:55:45.300
birth control pill in Puerto
Rico called La Operacion?

00:55:45.300 --> 00:55:49.065
It's sort of a far feminist
thing but very--shown very

00:55:49.065 --> 00:55:49.989
frequently.
 

00:55:49.989 --> 00:55:54.228
One of the places that the
birth control pill,

00:55:54.228 --> 00:55:59.219
invented in America,
was tested was in Puerto Rico.

00:55:59.219 --> 00:56:02.130
It shows a lot of people,
they're talking in Spanish,

00:56:02.130 --> 00:56:04.896
but there's a narrator speaking
in English which most everybody

00:56:04.896 --> 00:56:07.338
can understand,
and the narrator is saying how

00:56:07.338 --> 00:56:10.615
terrible everything is and that
these women weren't told what

00:56:10.615 --> 00:56:11.489
was going on.
 

00:56:11.489 --> 00:56:14.943
What you see when the narrator
is speaking is an older woman

00:56:14.943 --> 00:56:17.929
who wasn't eligible to be a
subject in the test,

00:56:17.929 --> 00:56:21.898
at night climbing into the
window at the basement of the

00:56:21.898 --> 00:56:25.795
hospital to get the birth
control pill and the narrator

00:56:25.795 --> 00:56:29.110
says nothing about that,
but they're showing this to you.

00:56:29.110 --> 00:56:30.659
Have you seen it?
 

00:56:30.659 --> 00:56:32.929
I saw--had sort of a hand up.
 

00:56:32.929 --> 00:56:35.842
In the U.S.,
among affluent,

00:56:35.842 --> 00:56:42.206
educated women that nobody is
presumably pushing around 13.8

00:56:42.206 --> 00:56:45.262
million--
women use tubal ligation,

00:56:45.262 --> 00:56:49.364
a female form of sterilization
as their method of birth control

00:56:49.364 --> 00:56:53.268
and less than that 13.2 million
were using the birth control

00:56:53.268 --> 00:56:53.929
pill.
 

00:56:53.929 --> 00:56:59.074
In the United States,
like in almost every other

00:56:59.074 --> 00:57:04.000
country, sterilization is the
chosen means.

00:57:04.000 --> 00:57:08.443
I think that's one indicator
that when people say they want

00:57:08.443 --> 00:57:11.510
reduced fertility they really
mean it.

00:57:11.510 --> 00:57:17.594
Sometimes family
planning--contraception is not

00:57:17.594 --> 00:57:24.474
available and then people can
get into very desperate

00:57:24.474 --> 00:57:26.460
situations.
 

00:57:26.460 --> 00:57:31.297
An American maternity nurse
went to Lusaka in Zambia and

00:57:31.297 --> 00:57:35.960
this is the University teaching
hospital in Zambia.

00:57:35.960 --> 00:57:38.597
So, most of these developed
countries will have a capital

00:57:38.597 --> 00:57:41.282
city and they have one high
class hospital that'll usually

00:57:41.282 --> 00:57:44.063
be attached to a university and
that's demanded by the upper

00:57:44.063 --> 00:57:46.655
class of that country,
the political elite,

00:57:46.655 --> 00:57:50.269
the economical elite demand
good modern medical services,

00:57:50.269 --> 00:57:52.309
it'll be one hospital there.
 

00:57:52.309 --> 00:57:55.746
You can look at the public
health budget for these

00:57:55.746 --> 00:57:59.184
countries and a very
disproportionate amount of it

00:57:59.184 --> 00:58:01.500
will go to this one hospital.
 

00:58:01.500 --> 00:58:05.373
This University teaching
hospital in Lusaka is the high

00:58:05.373 --> 00:58:07.309
level hospital in Zambia.
 

00:58:07.309 --> 00:58:09.719
This nurse went into the
maternity ward;

00:58:09.719 --> 00:58:14.005
she was a maternity nurse,
expecting to see a lot of women

00:58:14.005 --> 00:58:15.360
having children.
 

00:58:15.360 --> 00:58:18.280
Instead this is what--this is
her report.

00:58:18.280 --> 00:58:22.351
"Ten women with botched
abortions were lying on nine

00:58:22.351 --> 00:58:22.860
beds.
 

00:58:22.860 --> 00:58:26.248
Five others were sprawled on
the concrete floors of the

00:58:26.248 --> 00:58:26.940
hallways.
 

00:58:26.940 --> 00:58:30.579
A few more were in the hall--on
the floor outside the entrance.

00:58:30.579 --> 00:58:33.730
There were no blankets or
covers.

00:58:33.730 --> 00:58:37.639
Most wait 12 hours for
treatment from a physician.

00:58:37.639 --> 00:58:41.500
The 'average' woman ends up
overnight on the floor;

00:58:41.500 --> 00:58:44.539
she receives no food or water.
 

00:58:44.539 --> 00:58:48.137
The women were aborting on the
floors or on their way to the

00:58:48.137 --> 00:58:50.820
single toilet at the end of the
long hall;

00:58:50.820 --> 00:58:54.132
30% of the patients complete
their abortions on the concrete

00:58:54.132 --> 00:58:55.760
floor with no medical care.
 

00:58:55.760 --> 00:58:57.820
All we can do is clean it
up."

00:58:57.820 --> 00:59:02.222
That's what the head nurse
there said, that all we can do

00:59:02.222 --> 00:59:03.559
is clean it up.
 

00:59:03.559 --> 00:59:05.599
This is not isolated to this
one hospital.

00:59:05.599 --> 00:59:10.364
You can go anywhere in the
underdeveloped world and at

00:59:10.364 --> 00:59:16.030
least half the beds in maternity
wards are taken up with botched

00:59:16.030 --> 00:59:17.289
abortions.
 

00:59:17.289 --> 00:59:19.159
What goes on is,
in most of Africa,

00:59:19.159 --> 00:59:22.280
and a lot of the world,
abortion is illegal,

00:59:22.280 --> 00:59:25.795
so doctors can't do it,
so they go to what they call

00:59:25.795 --> 00:59:28.547
bush doctors,
some very poorly trained

00:59:28.547 --> 00:59:31.909
midwife or someone who just says
they'll do it,

00:59:31.909 --> 00:59:36.750
and they have this operation
and usually something is put up,

00:59:36.750 --> 00:59:40.804
a stick or coat hanger or
something up the uterus and they

00:59:40.804 --> 00:59:42.940
try to scrape out the fetus.
 

00:59:42.940 --> 00:59:45.608
But, in fact,
they often puncture the uterus

00:59:45.608 --> 00:59:49.268
which allows infection to get
into the main body cavity,

00:59:49.268 --> 00:59:53.235
and then after a few days
they're getting very sick from

00:59:53.235 --> 00:59:57.418
the infection which is now
systemic because it's inside the

00:59:57.418 --> 00:59:59.702
body,
plus the wound doesn't heal

00:59:59.702 --> 01:00:02.945
because of the infection so
there's constant bleeding and

01:00:02.945 --> 01:00:04.219
they can bleed out.
 

01:00:04.219 --> 01:00:06.072
Huge death rates,
we're going to talk about

01:00:06.072 --> 01:00:08.456
abortion later and I'll give you
some of these numbers,

01:00:08.456 --> 01:00:09.559
but huge death rates.
 

01:00:09.559 --> 01:00:13.739
Important point for this course
is that probably all of these

01:00:13.739 --> 01:00:17.989
women know of someone else who
has died from one of these--

01:00:17.989 --> 01:00:24.039
shall we call them
unprofessional abortions.

01:00:24.039 --> 01:00:28.824
Yet, when they get pregnant,
their desire not to have that

01:00:28.824 --> 01:00:33.777
extra child is so strong that
they will themselves choose to

01:00:33.777 --> 01:00:40.369
undergo this very,
very serious operation with a

01:00:40.369 --> 01:00:44.710
very high threat of death.
 

01:00:44.710 --> 01:00:49.175
That's one of the things that
the Planned Parent Federation in

01:00:49.175 --> 01:00:53.860
its international efforts like
what you saw is trying to cure.

01:00:53.860 --> 01:00:58.599
They had one project to go to
Kenya to train local private

01:00:58.599 --> 01:01:03.340
doctors who somewhat escape the
law in family planning and

01:01:03.340 --> 01:01:05.170
abortion services.
 

01:01:05.170 --> 01:01:07.972
The local doctors had been
turning away abortion clients

01:01:07.972 --> 01:01:10.469
because they did not know where
to refer them,

01:01:10.469 --> 01:01:15.599
so that means they got some
unskilled practitioner.

01:01:15.599 --> 01:01:18.702
One physician told the project
director that he had turned away

01:01:18.702 --> 01:01:21.657
a young girl only to find her in
a hospital a few days later

01:01:21.657 --> 01:01:24.010
after she had procured an
illegal abortion.

01:01:24.010 --> 01:01:25.840
The girl died.
 

01:01:25.840 --> 01:01:28.413
The private doctor said that he
had since then lived with a

01:01:28.413 --> 01:01:29.389
great deal of guilt.
 

01:01:29.389 --> 01:01:33.409
He is happy now that he can
provide treatment using a very

01:01:33.409 --> 01:01:34.610
safe procedure.
 

01:01:34.610 --> 01:01:39.702
In between that they've
legalized things to some degree

01:01:39.702 --> 01:01:40.739
in Kenya.
 

01:01:40.739 --> 01:01:43.960
It's not only the third world
in which this takes place.

01:01:43.960 --> 01:01:48.739
In Bulgaria,
sometime back under the Soviet

01:01:48.739 --> 01:01:54.090
system, 57% of pregnancies ended
in abortion.

01:01:54.090 --> 01:01:56.260
You'll hear during the abortion
lecture in the United States,

01:01:56.260 --> 01:01:59.659
there's one abortion for every
three live births,

01:01:59.659 --> 01:02:03.818
and something like 40 to 50
million abortions worldwide and

01:02:03.818 --> 01:02:08.409
about half of these are illegal
and illegal means very unsafe.

01:02:08.409 --> 01:02:11.434
A woman dies,
it's about every three minutes

01:02:11.434 --> 01:02:14.880
from a botched--one of these
illegal abortions.

01:02:14.880 --> 01:02:17.856
I think with these stories and
the large numbers that are

01:02:17.856 --> 01:02:20.246
attached to them,
I mean any woman in that

01:02:20.246 --> 01:02:24.853
situation that has an abortion,
she does not want that child

01:02:24.853 --> 01:02:30.519
and when you say there's 50
million of them worldwide that

01:02:30.519 --> 01:02:35.887
means that the demand for
control of fertility is very,

01:02:35.887 --> 01:02:37.380
very high.
 

01:02:37.380 --> 01:02:40.949
You'll read the Brazilian
solution to this which is a

01:02:40.949 --> 01:02:42.940
modern form of infanticide.
 

01:02:42.940 --> 01:02:45.114
I don't know if you read yet,
the Death Without

01:02:45.114 --> 01:02:48.494
Weeping,
it's in your reading packet

01:02:48.494 --> 01:02:54.728
where mothers who know that they
can't raise a child just leave

01:02:54.728 --> 01:03:00.659
the child to die and they say
that 'God can take better care

01:03:00.659 --> 01:03:06.190
of it then I can' and they just
let the child die.

01:03:06.190 --> 01:03:11.579
This is not to say that--So,
what has happened in the world

01:03:11.579 --> 01:03:17.342
is that fertility has come down
drastically and I've showed you

01:03:17.342 --> 01:03:23.289
that in previous graphs where
the fertility is coming down,

01:03:23.289 --> 01:03:28.579
and in the peak period in
Bolivia during the peak--

01:03:28.579 --> 01:03:33.311
the number doubled from about
12% to 25% of people using a

01:03:33.311 --> 01:03:34.639
modern method.
 

01:03:34.639 --> 01:03:38.929
Ecuador, 50% of the women are
using a modern mechanism.

01:03:38.929 --> 01:03:44.639
Tunisia, 60% and Iran is one of
the really interesting cases.

01:03:44.639 --> 01:03:48.592
Iran had this very conservative
government and they were against

01:03:48.592 --> 01:03:52.295
family planning and all this,
and then they had the war with

01:03:52.295 --> 01:03:52.860
Iraq.
 

01:03:52.860 --> 01:03:54.172
Iraq invaded,
with U.S.

01:03:54.172 --> 01:03:56.619
help, and huge numbers of
people died,

01:03:56.619 --> 01:04:00.001
including a lot of kids,
so afterwards their young

01:04:00.001 --> 01:04:03.039
people were depleted but once
those kids--

01:04:03.039 --> 01:04:04.780
they recovered a little bit
from that,

01:04:04.780 --> 01:04:08.563
the government realized what
was happening and decided on a

01:04:08.563 --> 01:04:10.260
family planning program.
 

01:04:10.260 --> 01:04:15.239
This is an Iranian woman
packing condoms.

01:04:15.239 --> 01:04:19.086
We have this image of places
like Iran as being so backwards

01:04:19.086 --> 01:04:22.139
and conservative and everything,
but they have,

01:04:22.139 --> 01:04:25.389
in fact, now one of the best
family planning programs in the

01:04:25.389 --> 01:04:27.972
world,
and the UN a few years ago

01:04:27.972 --> 01:04:32.635
awarded it their top--
best program in the world and

01:04:32.635 --> 01:04:37.579
their fertility rate is now at
replacement level.

01:04:37.579 --> 01:04:42.643
Fertility is coming down almost
everywhere, with again

01:04:42.643 --> 01:04:48.472
Sub-Saharan Africa and some of
the Arab countries as a counter

01:04:48.472 --> 01:04:49.619
example.
 

01:04:49.619 --> 01:04:52.150
Birth rates not only--Birth
rates fell;

01:04:52.150 --> 01:04:56.893
Thailand 50% in 12 years;
Columbia 40% in 14 years,

01:04:56.893 --> 01:04:58.679
this is at the peak.
 

01:04:58.679 --> 01:05:03.280
Indonesia 48% in 20 years;
Morocco 31% in 12 years;

01:05:03.280 --> 01:05:07.179
Turkey 21% in ten years;
Brazil 60% in 25 years;

01:05:07.179 --> 01:05:11.829
Mexico 30% in just six years;
Botswana 26%;

01:05:11.829 --> 01:05:14.992
Zimbabwe 18%;
Kenya 35%, I mean everywhere

01:05:14.992 --> 01:05:18.469
that you look the actual
fertility is coming down,

01:05:18.469 --> 01:05:23.552
so people are using
contraception and using it

01:05:23.552 --> 01:05:29.766
efficiently and the world birth
rate has come down quite

01:05:29.766 --> 01:05:31.800
significantly.
 

01:05:31.800 --> 01:05:36.829
None of this is to minimize
that people in developing

01:05:36.829 --> 01:05:42.313
countries are caught in a bind,
that you all have heard all

01:05:42.313 --> 01:05:47.269
kinds of reasons why they might
want to have a lot of children

01:05:47.269 --> 01:05:49.789
and one is extra farm labor.
 

01:05:49.789 --> 01:05:52.768
One is support for children in
old age, a major kind of

01:05:52.768 --> 01:05:53.320
problem.
 

01:05:53.320 --> 01:05:56.320
One their religion might demand
it.

01:05:56.320 --> 01:05:59.436
Two cultural reasons,
various ancestor worship

01:05:59.436 --> 01:06:00.130
reasons.
 

01:06:00.130 --> 01:06:04.193
In India you have to have a son
to light the funeral pyre,

01:06:04.193 --> 01:06:07.829
no son you don't go into the
afterworld properly.

01:06:07.829 --> 01:06:10.320
We discussed some of this with
respect to Africa.

01:06:10.320 --> 01:06:13.559
Status reasons,
you have more children you have

01:06:13.559 --> 01:06:16.940
more prestige for both the man
and the woman,

01:06:16.940 --> 01:06:21.992
there's macho reasons to prove
your fertility and the list goes

01:06:21.992 --> 01:06:22.969
on and on.
 

01:06:22.969 --> 01:06:27.128
The reasons they may not use
birth control are many,

01:06:27.128 --> 01:06:32.429
one of which is family planning
services can be very primitive.

01:06:32.429 --> 01:06:35.766
It's not a great slide but it's
an old bus in India with a red

01:06:35.766 --> 01:06:38.884
cross on it and this is the
family planning clinic in this

01:06:38.884 --> 01:06:40.579
part of India at that time.
 

01:06:40.579 --> 01:06:43.228
People were supposed to go on
this bus and have some operation

01:06:43.228 --> 01:06:45.139
that they didn't understand done
to them,

01:06:45.139 --> 01:06:48.400
sterilization or IUD insertion
or something,

01:06:48.400 --> 01:06:55.094
and you know you wouldn't be
exactly very anxious to get on

01:06:55.094 --> 01:06:56.710
to that bus.
 

01:06:56.710 --> 01:07:03.451
Another thing that I mentioned
last time with respect to

01:07:03.451 --> 01:07:07.309
Veena's lecture,
that the worry about medical

01:07:07.309 --> 01:07:10.697
complications is one of the most
major reasons why women either

01:07:10.697 --> 01:07:14.699
don't use contraception at all,
or start it and then stop using

01:07:14.699 --> 01:07:14.969
it.
 

01:07:14.969 --> 01:07:18.027
What does this mean in a
pre-medical country where they

01:07:18.027 --> 01:07:20.349
don't have really modern medical
ideas.

01:07:20.349 --> 01:07:22.539
You take the pill,
you're scared of it.

01:07:22.539 --> 01:07:25.621
Anything that happens to you,
you get a tummy ache,

01:07:25.621 --> 01:07:29.072
you fall and break your leg,
anything that happens to you

01:07:29.072 --> 01:07:30.429
what do you blame?
 

01:07:30.429 --> 01:07:31.820
You blame the pill.
 

01:07:31.820 --> 01:07:33.840
So here is a culture without
much medicine,

01:07:33.840 --> 01:07:36.829
a low standard of living;
they're getting sick a lot.

01:07:36.829 --> 01:07:40.262
People in developing countries
are not generally very healthy

01:07:40.262 --> 01:07:43.809
and they get sick and they don't
know what it was caused by.

01:07:43.809 --> 01:07:46.099
You probably read already about
The Evil Eye.

01:07:46.099 --> 01:07:49.050
Did you read the Egyptian--the
Kul Khaal yet?

01:07:49.050 --> 01:07:50.710
The Evil Eye is the reason.
 

01:07:50.710 --> 01:07:53.434
If you've taken the pill you
know that's changing your body

01:07:53.434 --> 01:07:55.353
in some way,
and you're afraid of it,

01:07:55.353 --> 01:07:58.577
you get sick with anything,
it's the pill was the reason

01:07:58.577 --> 01:08:02.278
for it and then you tell all
your friends that and everybody

01:08:02.278 --> 01:08:05.918
in the community learns that
such and such got some problem

01:08:05.918 --> 01:08:09.496
because of the pill so they're
very much afraid to use the

01:08:09.496 --> 01:08:10.250
pill.
 

01:08:10.250 --> 01:08:16.698
On an on, there's a big
conflict, big contestation,

01:08:16.698 --> 01:08:21.010
the media, I think this is in
Morocco,

01:08:21.010 --> 01:08:27.288
this is a cave,
this is the desert around here,

01:08:27.288 --> 01:08:29.979
they're in a cave and what
they're watching is a TV show.

01:08:29.979 --> 01:08:34.194
I was in Morocco in the far
desert and you see these little

01:08:34.194 --> 01:08:38.192
villages of just a few mud
houses and they all had solar

01:08:38.192 --> 01:08:41.100
arrays and they all had
television,

01:08:41.100 --> 01:08:44.319
so media is passing on very
strongly.

01:08:44.319 --> 01:08:47.631
On the other side of the
equation is all kinds of reasons

01:08:47.631 --> 01:08:50.470
that they don't use it or that
they do use it.

01:08:50.470 --> 01:08:53.050
It's a very much in
contestation.

01:08:53.050 --> 01:08:57.760
In the West,
especially activists,

01:08:57.760 --> 01:09:00.827
liberal people,
people in the Forestry School

01:09:00.827 --> 01:09:04.801
believe that we shouldn't
support family planning programs

01:09:04.801 --> 01:09:07.658
because it's politically
contentious.

01:09:07.658 --> 01:09:09.310
Why is it politically
contentious?

01:09:09.310 --> 01:09:12.109
Because people on the right are
opposed to it for religious or

01:09:12.109 --> 01:09:14.170
moral reasons,
people on the more or less

01:09:14.170 --> 01:09:16.435
left, and these are
characterizations right and

01:09:16.435 --> 01:09:16.829
left.
 

01:09:16.829 --> 01:09:20.407
We can't impose;
we 'great white Westerners'

01:09:20.407 --> 01:09:24.355
can't impose our values on our
'poor little yellow and brown

01:09:24.355 --> 01:09:25.158
cousins'.
 

01:09:25.158 --> 01:09:29.002
It's utter nonsense and it's
patronizing because the people

01:09:29.002 --> 01:09:32.846
in these developing countries
have spoken very clearly when

01:09:32.846 --> 01:09:35.828
they add up all these pluses and
minuses.

01:09:35.828 --> 01:09:39.948
That's their choice,
and as I've showed data--

01:09:39.948 --> 01:09:43.201
I've hit you over the head with
data showing you that when

01:09:43.201 --> 01:09:46.338
people in the developing
countries themselves add up the

01:09:46.338 --> 01:09:48.961
data,
they want to be protected by

01:09:48.961 --> 01:09:50.060
contraception.
 

01:09:50.060 --> 01:09:51.903
I think that we,
in the West,

01:09:51.903 --> 01:09:54.340
ought to take that very
seriously,

01:09:54.340 --> 01:09:57.479
and starting with intellectuals
who should know better,

01:09:57.479 --> 01:10:00.948
but since people don't give
courses like this and people--

01:10:00.948 --> 01:10:03.828
even environmentalists and all
kinds of others,

01:10:03.828 --> 01:10:07.443
just don't pay any attention to
human population because it's

01:10:07.443 --> 01:10:09.010
politically untouchable.
 

01:10:09.010 --> 01:10:12.193
The major organizations,
the environmental organizations

01:10:12.193 --> 01:10:15.434
won't touch it because they do
fundraising and the public

01:10:15.434 --> 01:10:19.429
opinion is that--
it's a horrible thing to push

01:10:19.429 --> 01:10:23.359
family planning on developing
countries.

01:10:23.359 --> 01:10:32.020
I guess that is where we will
end today.

01:10:32.020 --> 01:10:35.359
See you--yes one more this week
